The paper focuses on improving the interpretability of deep neural networks for video captioning, which is a task related to computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel technique that involves integrating semantic information into the model and using an interpretive loss, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed technique on video data, which is a subfield of multimedia (MM).
